Event Itinerary

Day 1: Ideation & Persuasion

  • 9:00 AM – 9:45 AM

    Orientation & Icebreaker

    Welcome, event briefing, and randomized team formation (5 members per team).

  • 9:45 AM – 12:30 PM

    Core Session: Entrepreneurial & Design Thinking

    Learn to spot opportunities and use design thinking to define problems. Tracks introduced: FinTech, AI, Agritech, etc.
    Team Task: Prepare and submit a Problem Canvas (15% of evaluation).

  • 12:30 PM – 1:30 PM

    ☕ Lunch Break

  • 1:30 PM – 2:00 PM

    Assignment Submission & Prep

    Teams finalize and submit their Problem Canvas.

  • 2:00 PM – 3:00 PM

    Session: Sales & Psychology

    Build confidence by learning the basics of persuasion and customer psychology.

  • 3:00 PM – 4:00 PM

    Interactive Drill: Random Sales Pitch

    Teams nominate one member to pitch a random item in a 2-minute impromptu drill.

  • 4:00 PM – 5:00 PM

    🎤 Round 1 Presentations + Feedback

    Each team presents their Problem Canvas (3 min pitch + 2 min Q&A) and receives constructive feedback from judges.

Day 2: Storytelling & Finals

  • 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM

    Session: Storytelling & Pitching

    Learn how to structure a compelling pitch and turn ideas into powerful stories.

  • 10:00 AM – 12:30 PM

    🎤 Round 1: Preliminary Pitches

    Each team delivers a 3-minute pitch. Judges evaluate and shortlist the top 5 teams for the Final Round.

  • 12:30 PM – 1:30 PM

    ☕ Lunch Break

  • 1:30 PM – 2:30 PM

    Finalists’ Preparation Time

    The 5 shortlisted teams refine their presentations with dedicated mentor feedback.

  • 2:30 PM – 4:30 PM

    🏆 Round 2: Final Pitches

    Each finalist team gets 7 minutes to pitch, followed by a 3-minute Q&A. An audience vote is also held for the People’s Choice Award.

  • 4:30 PM – 5:00 PM

    Closing & Awards Ceremony

    Announcement of winners for Best Pitch, Most Creative Idea, Best Storytelling, and Audience Favorite.
